The global home blood pressure monitors market is expected to witness significant growth during the forecast period of 2021 to 2030. Factors such as the increasing prevalence of hypertension, rising awareness about preventive healthcare, and the growing geriatric population are driving the market's growth. The convenience and ease of monitoring blood pressure at home, especially in the wake of the COVID-19 pandemic, have further fueled the adoption of home blood pressure monitors. Additionally, technological advancements such as wireless connectivity and smartphone integration have made these devices more user-friendly and efficient, contributing to market growth.

